            <h4>What is the current population of Montgomery?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Montgomery is 1,257.  Montgomery, West Virginia is the 9,363rd largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Montgomery?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Montgomery was in
                    1990, when its population was
                    2,434.
                    
                        In 1990, Montgomery was the
                        6,207th largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 9,363rd largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Montgomery is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            48.4%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 1990.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Montgomery shrinking?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Montgomery has shrunk
                        35.1% 
                        since the year 2000.
                    


                    
                        Montgomery, West Virginia's growth is extremely below
                        average.
                        100% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
